Those are my config files. I hope they are useful for someone but don't come crying if something breaks on your system because of them

# Installing the configuration files on a new machine

    git clone git@github.com:nikolavp/configs.git
    cd config && ./install.sh


# Full configuration

To properly use the environment you will have to install a bunch of other packages. If you are on Debian based system try the following

    cat bg-dvorak-phonetic >> /usr/share/X11/xkb/symbols/bg
    sudo apt-get install -y subversion vim-gtk awesome awesome-extra zshell tmux gtk-redshift xscreensaver xscreensaver-data-extra xscreensaver-gl-extra parcellite xbindkeys

check out gcalci(https://github.com/insanum/gcalcli) to see my calendar application
